  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "MAPF can basically be formulated as a Markov Game (MG), an extension of the Markov Decision Process (MDP) framework to capture decision-making in multi-agent settings (Littman 1994).",
    "An MDP is represented by a 5-tuple < S, A, T, ℜ, 𝛾 >, where",
    "• S is the state space, • A is the action space, • T ∶ S × A → P(S) is the state transition distribution function, • ℜ ∶ S × A → ℝ is the reward function, and • ∈ [0, 1] is the discount factor.",
    "The objective of an MDP is to select actions that maximize the expected long-term cumulative reward, considering an unknown transition function T and the reward func- tion ℜ.",
    "The agent learns a behavior policy ∶ S → P(A) that optimizes the expected performance G throughout the learning process."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "MAPF can basically be formulated as a Markov Game (MG), an extension of the Markov Decision Process (MDP) framework to capture decision-making in multi-agent settings (Littman 1994)."
  ]
